  "text": "Here, the arrows denote the right-going and the left-going components of the total waveform. Assuming that the signals are bandlimited to half of sampling rate, we may sample the traveling waves without losing any information by selecting T as the sample interval and X the position interval between samples so that T = X/c. Sampling is applied in a discrete time-space grid in which n and k are related to time and position, respectively. The discretized version of (3) becomes [CITATION_1] :",
